  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1190688604" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1190688604" />
    <a title="Jim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/439937-jim"><img alt="Jim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1328297665p2/439937.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1190688604?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jim" href="/user/show/439937-jim">Jim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/439937-jim?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/439937-jim?shelf=war">war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1190688604" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3896157655925671867">A solid piece of military history that details the bloodiest battle of the Civil War and one that perhaps saved the Union, or at least showed they could stand up to Lee. It certainly stopped the Confederate incursion into Maryland, though McClellan could have achieved a heavier victory if he had pursued Lee or even committed more of his troops at critical times. I am always amazed by how soldiers could march into the face of the weaponry they had then. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


